ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Mark the line (0-100) with an X at the point that summarizes your overall sense of well-being for the past 24 hours
Notes: 0= Worst you have ever been; 100= Best you have ever been

ElementDescription: Mark the line (0-100) with an X at the point that summarizes your overall sense of well-being for the entire month
Notes: 0= Worst you have ever been; 100= Best you have ever been

ElementDescription: Mark the line (1-10) with an X at the point that summarizes your overall sense of well-being for the past 24 hours
Notes: 1= Worst you have ever been; 10= Best you have ever been

ElementDescription: Mark the line (1-10) with an X at the point that summarizes your overall sense of well-being for the entire month
Notes: 1= Worst you have ever been; 10= Best you have ever been
